    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Magnificent state beds used in the ceremonial bedrooms of a noble or royal residence, coined in 18th-century French usage. Such beds were not intended to be used for routine sleeping, but for example, for the display of a royal newborn with his mother, of the sick or dying monarch, etc.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093897/Metropolitan Museum of Art [online] (2001-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Término francés del siglo XVIII para majestuosas camas de respeto usadas en los dormitorios ceremoniales de una residencia real. No estaban destinadas a usarse para dormir.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Franse benaming uit de 18e eeuw die wordt gebruikt voor indrukwekkende staatsbedden in ceremoniële slaapkamers van koninklijke verblijfplaatsen; niet bedoeld om in te slapen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>此類華麗的御用床置於十八世紀法國皇室或官邸的儀式性臥房，該類床不用於日常臥寢，而用於如展示皇室的新生兒與母親、生病或病危的國王等其他目的。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
